Introduced
Second Regular Session 124th General Assembly (2026)
SENATE CONCURRENT
RESOLUTION No. _____
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION celebrating the 20th
2 anniversary of Hope Academy.
3 Whereas, Hope Academy is a tuition-free public charter
4 school that opened in 2006 to give teens struggling with drugs
5 and alcohol a place to continue their education while focusing
6 on recovery;
7 Whereas, Hope Academy is Indiana's only recovery high
8 school and one of just twelve schools in the country accredited
9 by the Association of Recovery Schools;
10 Whereas, Nationally, nearly 80% of students relapse after
11 going back to their school following substance use disorder
12 treatment, however at Hope Academy, students get both a
13 strong education and daily recovery support;
14 Whereas, Hope Academy has built a supportive community
15 of parents, caregivers, and staff to give these students the
16 guidance and connection needed to succeed in their recovery;
17 Whereas, As part of its 20th anniversary, Hope Academy
18 has launched its Sustainability Campaign to strengthen
19 academic and recovery programs, expand family supports, and
20 secure the long-term future of the school to continue changing
21 the lives of teens in recovery for the next 20 years and beyond;
22 Whereas, Since 2006, Hope Academy has helped over 800
23 students, with 50 teens enrolling annually, and over 200
24 graduates, with 94% of graduates getting accepted into post-
2026 RC 1527/DI JR

2
1 secondary programs; and
2 Whereas, Hope Academy has given hundreds of teens
3 across Marion, Boone, Hamilton, Hancock, Hendricks,
4 Johnson, Madison, Morgan, and Shelby counties the
5 opportunity to better their lives through recovery and
6 continuing their education, allowing them to live healthy,
7 productive lives: Therefore,
8 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly
9 of the State of Indiana, the House of Representatives
10 concurring:
11 SECTION 1. That the Indiana General Assembly celebrates
12 the 20th anniversary of Hope Academy.
13 SECTION 2. The Secretary of the Senate is hereby directed
14 to transmit copies of this Resolution to Senator Carrasco.
